%% CiteGuard Audit Log Hash Chain Construction
%% Last updated by ADR-0003 on 2026-04-18

sequenceDiagram
    participant Caller as State-Changing Operation
    participant ALS as AuditLogService
    participant DB as Postgres (audit_log)
    participant Hasher as SHA-256 Hasher

    Note over Caller, DB: Every state change writes audit entry in SAME transaction

    Caller->>ALS: append(event_type, actor, payload, firm_id)

    ALS->>DB: SELECT this_hash FROM audit_log<br/>WHERE firm_id = :firm_id<br/>ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 1

    alt First entry for firm (genesis)
        DB-->>ALS: NULL (no prior row)
        ALS->>Hasher: sha256("")
        Hasher-->>ALS: genesis_hash
        Note over ALS: prior_hash = sha256("")
    else Subsequent entry
        DB-->>ALS: prior_row.this_hash
        Note over ALS: prior_hash = prior_row.this_hash
    end

    ALS->>ALS: canonical_json(payload)<br/>- sorted keys<br/>- UTF-8 NFC normalized<br/>- stable numerics

    ALS->>Hasher: sha256(prior_hash || canonical_json(payload))
    Hasher-->>ALS: this_hash

    ALS->>DB: INSERT INTO audit_log<br/>(id, firm_id, document_id,<br/>event_type, actor_user_id,<br/>payload, prior_hash, this_hash,<br/>created_at)

    Note over DB: REVOKE UPDATE, DELETE on audit_log<br/>DB role prevents modification

    ALS-->>Caller: audit_entry_id

    Note over ALS, DB: Daily Verification Job

    rect rgb(255, 240, 240)
        ALS->>DB: SELECT * FROM audit_log<br/>WHERE firm_id = :firm_id<br/>ORDER BY created_at ASC
        loop For each row
            ALS->>Hasher: Recompute: sha256(prior_hash || canonical_json(payload))
            Hasher-->>ALS: computed_hash
            ALS->>ALS: Compare computed_hash == this_hash
            alt Hash mismatch
                ALS->>ALS: ALERT: P0 Incident<br/>Hash chain integrity violation
            end
        end
    end
